        "description": "The modeled QoI (normalized hemolysis index, scalar shear stress integral) must be demonstrably linked to the clinical endpoint (pump-induced hemolysis) via a documented mechanistic or empirical relationship."
      },
      "rationale": "The normalized hemolysis index (NHI) is derived from the power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.) relating shear stress magnitude and exposure time to red cell damage. This model is widely accepted in the blood pump literature and directly predicts the clinically measured plasma-free hemoglobin index. QoI relevance is established."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/cf-07-relevance-validation",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
